meta {
  name: report
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/report
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "device_id": "{{device_id}}",
    "previous_hash": "aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa",
    "new_hash":      "bbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbb",
    "success": true,
    "timestamp": 1746000000
  }
}

docs {
  Post-update report. The agent calls this after a swap+restart cycle
  completes — whether the new binary booted healthy (success=true) or the
  watchdog rolled back (success=false, rollback_reason set).

  Response: 202 Accepted with an empty body. The server logs the report at
  INFO; there's no downstream consumer in this release (hook it up to
  your fleet dashboard if you have one).

  Fields on rollback look like:
    {
      "device_id":"...",
      "previous_hash":"<new binary hash>",
      "new_hash":"<rolled-back-to hash>",
      "success": false,
      "rollback_reason": "health check failed: ...",
      "timestamp": ...
    }
}
